  <reg:NIF>AMENDMENTS NOT IN FORCE</reg:NIF>
  <reg:acttitle>Animal Health Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Fur Farm Regulation<in:br/> B.C. Reg. 8/2015</reg:title>
  <reg:NIFby>amended by B.C. Reg. 295/2021</reg:NIFby>
  <reg:NIFdate>effective April 1, 2025</reg:NIFdate>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:schedule>
      <bcl:scheduletitle>Schedule 5</bcl:scheduletitle>
      <bcl:lefttext>
        <in:strong>
          <in:em>1	Section 1 of the Fur Farm Regulation, B.C. Reg. 8/2015, is amended by repealing the definitions of <in:term>licence</in:term> and <in:term>mink pelt licence</in:term>.</in:em>
        </in:strong>
      </bcl:lefttext>
      <bcl:lefttext>
        <in:strong>
          <in:em>2	Section 2 (2.1) is repealed and the following substituted:</in:em>
        </in:strong>
      </bcl:lefttext>
      <bcl:indent1>(2.1)	A person must not engage in fur farming of mink, including keeping or dealing with mink pelts.</bcl:indent1>
      <bcl:lefttext>
        <in:strong>
          <in:em>3	Sections 2.1, 4.1, 4.2 and 4.3 are repealed.</in:em>
        </in:strong>
      </bcl:lefttext>
      <bcl:lefttext>
        <in:strong>
          <in:em>4	Sections 5 and 6 (1) are amended by striking out "</in:em>
        </in:strong>licence<in:strong><in:em>" wherever it appears and substituting "</in:em></in:strong>fur farm licence<in:strong><in:em>".</in:em></in:strong></bcl:lefttext>
      <bcl:lefttext>
        <in:strong>
          <in:em>5	Section 19 (b.1) is repealed.</in:em>
        </in:strong>
      </bcl:lefttext>
    </bcl:schedule>
  </reg:content>
</reg:regulation>